      "content": "It is completely understandable to feel overwhelmed, as delays often feel like a domino effect where one small disruption triggers a chain reaction of missed connections and rebooking nightmares. This chaos is largely due to the fragility of global airline schedules, which rely on tight coordination between hundreds of aircraft, pilots, and crew across multiple time zones. When a single flight cancels, it doesn't just affect that one passenger; it ripples through the airline's entire network, forcing sudden changes to hundreds of other bookings simultaneously.\n\nHowever, the situation is actually quite systematic, even when it feels random, because airlines have dedicated ground handling teams and rebooking centers working specifically to manage these cascading failures. Instead of viewing the chaos as \"breaking for no reason,\" try to see it as a massive, high-speed puzzle being solved in real-time by human employees who are also stressed but working to get you to your destination.\n\nIf you are feeling stuck, remember that the goal isn't to solve the entire global airline crisis in your head right this second, but simply to focus on the next immediate step, like finding the flight information kiosk or asking a staff member at the desk for the very next available seat. You are safe, and while the process feels dis",
